{"id":235261,"date":"2024-01-30T03:19:49","date_gmt":"2024-01-29T21:49:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=235261"},"modified":"2024-02-01T13:35:17","modified_gmt":"2024-02-01T08:05:17","slug":"vijay-kumar-sinha","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/","title":{"rendered":"Vijay Kumar Sinha Wiki, Age, Caste, Wife, Family, Biography &#038; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-235512 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha\" width=\"601\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha.jpg 601w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-65x65.jpg 65w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 601px) 100vw, 601px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Vijay Kumar Sinha is an Indian politician and a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP). He was elected MLA from Lakhisarai in 2005, 2010, 2015, and 2020. He held the position of Speaker in the Bihar Legislative Assembly from 2020 to 2022. He stepped down from this role after a no-confidence motion was moved against him by the then-ruling Mahagathbandhan. He has served as Leader of the Opposition Bihar Legislative Assembly (2022-2024) and Minister of Labour Resources Government of Bihar (2017-2020). He started serving as one of Bihar&#8217;s Deputy Chief Ministers in 2024, along with Samrat Choudhary sharing the role, under the leadership of <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/nitish-kumar\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Nitish Kumar<\/a> as the Chief Minister.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce1571e4fc\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce1571e4fc\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Family_Caste\" title=\"Family &amp; Caste\">Family &amp; Caste<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Wife_Children\" title=\"Wife &amp; Children\">Wife &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Religion\" title=\"Religion\">Religion<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#SignatureAutograph\" title=\"Signature\/Autograph\">Signature\/Autograph<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Car_Collection\" title=\"Car Collection\">Car Collection<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Assets_Liabilities\" title=\"Assets &amp; Liabilities\">Assets &amp; Liabilities<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-11\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Movable_Assets\" title=\"Movable Assets\">Movable Assets<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-12\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Immovable_Assets\" title=\"Immovable Assets\">Immovable Assets<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-13\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#Net_Worth\" title=\"Net Worth\">Net Worth<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-14\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/vijay-kumar-sinha\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Vijay Kumar Sinha was born on Monday, 5 June 1967 (<strong>age 56 years; as of 2023<\/strong>) in Tilakpur, Chanan Lakhisarai, Bihar, his maternal grandparents&#8217; village. His zodiac sign is Gemini. His family hails from Badpur in Mokama Block in the Patna District of Bihar. He pursued a Diploma in civil engineering at the Government Polytechnic, Barauni, Begusarai (1989). <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_235261_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/news\/politics-and-nation\/bihar-vijay-kumar-sinha-a-versatile-upper-caste-bjp-leader\/articleshow\/107204761.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/span><\/span> He was an active member of the Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad, the RSS&#8217; student wing during his college days. He became a volunteer of Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) in his formative days.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235879\" style=\"width: 440px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/An-old-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-father.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235879\" class=\" wp-image-235879\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/An-old-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-father.jpg\" alt=\"An old picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha with his father\" width=\"430\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/An-old-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-father.jpg 689w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/An-old-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-father-300x261.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 430px) 100vw, 430px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235879\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">An old picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha with his father<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 1982, he served as Secretary of the Durga Puja Committee, Barh. In 1983, he began his active participation in student politics joining Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad at A.N.S College, Barh. In 1985, he was the President of the Government Polytechnic Muzaffarpur Students Union and Secretary and Executive President of the Bihar Polytechnic Students Union. In 1988, he became the General Secretary of the Unemployed Bihar Junior Engineers Association.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Height (approx.):<\/strong> 5&#8242; 4&#8243;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour: <\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour: <\/strong>Black<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-picture.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-235874\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-picture.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha\" width=\"443\" height=\"506\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-picture.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-picture-262x300.jpg 262w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 443px) 100vw, 443px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family_Caste\"><\/span>Family &amp; Caste<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Sinha belongs to the Bhumihar community, an upper caste in Bihar. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_235261_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/news\/politics-and-nation\/bihar-vijay-kumar-sinha-a-versatile-upper-caste-bjp-leader\/articleshow\/107204761.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Vijay Kumar Sinha&#8217;s father, Sharada Raman Singh (deceased), was the headmaster of a high school in Berhna (Barh), Bihar. His mother&#8217;s name is Surma Devi.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235509\" style=\"width: 295px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-poster-featuring-the-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-father-Sharada-Raman-Singh.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235509\" class=\" wp-image-235509\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-poster-featuring-the-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-father-Sharada-Raman-Singh.jpg\" alt=\"A poster featuring the picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha's father, Sharada Raman Singh\" width=\"285\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-poster-featuring-the-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-father-Sharada-Raman-Singh.jpg 543w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-poster-featuring-the-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-father-Sharada-Raman-Singh-204x300.jpg 204w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 285px) 100vw, 285px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235509\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha&#8217;s father, Sharada Raman Singh<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_235859\" style=\"width: 368px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-sister.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235859\" class=\" wp-image-235859\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-sister.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha with his sister\" width=\"358\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-sister.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-sister-270x300.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 358px) 100vw, 358px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235859\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha with his sister<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Wife_Children\"><\/span><strong>Wife &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>On 8 June 1986, at the age of 19, he got married to Sushila Devi.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235876\" style=\"width: 438px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-wedding-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235876\" class=\" wp-image-235876\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-wedding-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha.jpg\" alt=\"A wedding picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha\" width=\"428\" height=\"526\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-wedding-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-wedding-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-244x300.jpg 244w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235876\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A wedding picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_235507\" style=\"width: 419px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-Sushila-Devi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235507\" class=\" wp-image-235507\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-Sushila-Devi.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha with his wife, Sushila Devi\" width=\"409\" height=\"662\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-Sushila-Devi.jpg 494w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-Sushila-Devi-185x300.jpg 185w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 409px) 100vw, 409px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235507\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha with his wife, Sushila Devi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Together, they have two sons and two daughters. One of his sons&#8217; names is E. Kanhaiya Bhardwaj. He got married to Dr. Shivangi in 2022.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235861\" style=\"width: 426px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-and-son.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235861\" class=\" wp-image-235861\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-and-son.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha with his wife and son\" width=\"416\" height=\"520\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-and-son.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-with-his-wife-and-son-240x300.jpg 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 416px) 100vw, 416px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235861\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha with his wife and son<\/p><\/div>\n<div id=\"attachment_235508\" style=\"width: 422px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-posing-with-his-son-E.-Kanhaiya-Bhardwaj-and-daughter-in-law-on-their-wedding-day-in-2022.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235508\" class=\" wp-image-235508\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-posing-with-his-son-E.-Kanhaiya-Bhardwaj-and-daughter-in-law-on-their-wedding-day-in-2022.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha posing with his son E. Kanhaiya Bhardwaj and daughter-in-law on their wedding day in 2022\" width=\"412\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-posing-with-his-son-E.-Kanhaiya-Bhardwaj-and-daughter-in-law-on-their-wedding-day-in-2022.jpg 637w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-posing-with-his-son-E.-Kanhaiya-Bhardwaj-and-daughter-in-law-on-their-wedding-day-in-2022-300x283.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 412px) 100vw, 412px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235508\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha posing with his son E. Kanhaiya Bhardwaj and daughter-in-law on their wedding day in 2022<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Religion\"><\/span>Religion<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>He follows Hinduism.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235510\" style=\"width: 632px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-performing-Chhath-Pooja-with-his-family.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235510\" class=\" wp-image-235510\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-performing-Chhath-Pooja-with-his-family.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha performing Chhath Pooja with his family\" width=\"622\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-performing-Chhath-Pooja-with-his-family.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-performing-Chhath-Pooja-with-his-family-300x135.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-performing-Chhath-Pooja-with-his-family-768x346.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 622px) 100vw, 622px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235510\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha performing Chhath Pooja with his family<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"SignatureAutograph\"><\/span>Signature\/Autograph<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_235511\" style=\"width: 580px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-signature.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235511\" class=\" wp-image-235511\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-signature.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha's signature\" width=\"570\" height=\"186\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-signature.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-signature-300x98.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinhas-signature-768x251.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235511\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha&#8217;s signature<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Vijay Kumar Sinha entered politics joining BJP in 1988. Thereafter, he served in various capacities, General Secretary of the Unemployed Bihar Junior Engineers Association (1988), President of Ward-8 Rajendra Nagar Mandal, Patna Metropolitan City (1988), Vice President of Rajendra Nagar Mandal, Patna Metropolitan BJP (1990), and President of Lok Nayak Mandal, Patna Metropolitan BJP (1992). He became in-charge cum working committee member of Patna metropolis in 1995 and State Council Member, District Lakhisarai, BJP in 1998. From 1999 to 2000, he served as a Member of Nehru Yuva Kendra Bihar. He was the election incharge of BJP, Suryagarh VS, District Lakhisarai during the 2000 Bihar Legislative Assembly election. Other positions that he served before becoming an MLA include State Secretary, Bharatiya Janata Yuva Morcha, Bihar (2002), State Working Committee Member, BJP, Bihar (2004), State General Secretary, Kisan Morcha, BJP, Bihar (2006). In 2005, the Bihar Assembly elections took place twice since no government could be formed in Bihar in the February election. Bihar was compelled to conduct another round of elections in October\u2013November of the same year. Vijay Kumar Sinha was elected as MLA from Lakhisarai in the February 2005 Bihar Legislative Assembly elections. However, RJD candidate Phulena Singh was elected as MLA from Lakhisarai in the October 2005 Bihar Legislative Assembly election, defeating Sinha by a short margin of 80 votes. The Janata Dal (United) emerged as the majority seat winner after the Oct- Nov 2005 election, and ruled along with the BJP as part of the National Democratic Alliance (NDA). Nitish Kumar was sworn in as the CM for the second time. In 2009, he was the Regional Incharge (Begusarai, Khagaria) of the BJP of Bihar State, and in 2013, he became the State Spokesperson of the BJP of Bihar State.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235881\" style=\"width: 518px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-at-Jilla-Prashasan-Begusarai.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235881\" class=\" wp-image-235881\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-at-Jilla-Prashasan-Begusarai.jpg\" alt=\"A picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha at Jilla Prashasan Begusarai\" width=\"508\" height=\"340\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-at-Jilla-Prashasan-Begusarai.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-at-Jilla-Prashasan-Begusarai-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/A-picture-of-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-at-Jilla-Prashasan-Begusarai-768x514.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 508px) 100vw, 508px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235881\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">A picture of Vijay Kumar Sinha at Jilla Prashasan Begusarai<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 2010, Vijay Kumar Sinha was re-elected as MLA from Lakhisarai, defeating RJD candidate Fulaina Singh by 59620 votes. In 2013, he was the Chairman of the Sub-Divisional Monitoring Committee, District Lakhisarai. In 2015, he was re-elected as MLA from Lakhisarai, defeating Janata Dal (United) candidate Ramanand Mandal by 6,556 votes. On 29 July 2017, he became Minister of Labour Resources, Government of Bihar; he served in this capacity till 16 November 2020. In 2018, he served as Chairman of the monitoring committee of Lakhisarai district.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235516\" style=\"width: 600px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-greeting-Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235516\" class=\" wp-image-235516\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-greeting-Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha greeting Prime Minister Narendra Modi\" width=\"590\" height=\"429\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-greeting-Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-greeting-Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi-300x218.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-greeting-Prime-Minister-Narendra-Modi-768x559.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235516\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha greeting Prime Minister Narendra Modi<\/p><\/div>\n<p>In 2020, he was re-elected as MLA from Lakhisarai, defeating INC candidate Amaresh Kumar by 10,483 votes. On 25 November 2020, Vijay Kumar Sinha, an NDA candidate, was elected as the Speaker of the Bihar Legislative Assembly through a voice vote amid high drama. The election took place amid chaos after the opposition demanded that it be conducted by secret ballot. Additionally, the Mahagathbandhan, led by the Rashtriya Janata Dal, objected to Chief Minister <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/nitish-kumar\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Nitish Kumar<\/a>&#8216;s attendance during the vote, citing that he is not a member of the House. The demands were turned down by the Chair, leading to protests by the opposition during which the house had to be adjourned. In the 243-member Assembly, Sinha received 126 votes in favour, while 114 members voted against him, with a total of 240 members participating in the vote.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235515\" style=\"width: 596px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-during-a-political-rally.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235515\" class=\" wp-image-235515\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-during-a-political-rally.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha during a political rally\" width=\"586\" height=\"364\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-during-a-political-rally.jpg 1020w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-during-a-political-rally-300x186.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-during-a-political-rally-768x477.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 586px) 100vw, 586px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235515\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha during a political rally<\/p><\/div>\n<p>On 24 August 2022, Sinha resigned from the post after a 20-month stint in the Chair after a no-confidence motion was moved against him by the then-ruling Mahagathbandhan. Thereafter, Nitish established the Mahagathbandhan government in collaboration with the RJD and Congress. In a surprising turn, the BJP nominated Sinha as the Leader of Opposition (LoP) on 24 August 2022, ahead of expected choices such as former Deputy CMs Tarkishor Prasad and Renu Devi. Sinha&#8217;s selection marked him as the third upper-caste leader chosen by the BJP for this role since 1995, following Yashwant Sinha and Ashwini Kumar Choubey.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235514\" style=\"width: 616px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Leader-of-Opposition-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-addresses-the-media-after-staging-a-walkout-during-the-budget-session-of-state-assembly-in-Patna-on-5-April-2023.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235514\" class=\" wp-image-235514\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Leader-of-Opposition-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-addresses-the-media-after-staging-a-walkout-during-the-budget-session-of-state-assembly-in-Patna-on-5-April-2023.jpg\" alt=\"Leader of Opposition Vijay Kumar Sinha addresses the media after staging a walkout during the budget session of state assembly in Patna on 5 April 2023\" width=\"606\" height=\"401\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Leader-of-Opposition-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-addresses-the-media-after-staging-a-walkout-during-the-budget-session-of-state-assembly-in-Patna-on-5-April-2023.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Leader-of-Opposition-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-addresses-the-media-after-staging-a-walkout-during-the-budget-session-of-state-assembly-in-Patna-on-5-April-2023-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Leader-of-Opposition-Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-addresses-the-media-after-staging-a-walkout-during-the-budget-session-of-state-assembly-in-Patna-on-5-April-2023-768x508.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 606px) 100vw, 606px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235514\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Leader of Opposition Vijay Kumar Sinha addresses the media after staging a walkout during the budget session of the state assembly in Patna on 5 April 2023<\/p><\/div>\n<p>On 28 January 2024, Samrat Choudhary and Vijay Kumar Sinha took oath as the new Deputy Chief Ministers of Bihar after CM Nitish Kumar did one of his regular U-turns and joined hands with the BJP once again.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_235513\" style=\"width: 721px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-taking-oath-as-the-new-Deputy-Chief-Ministers-of-Bihar-under-the-leadership-of-Nitish-Kumar-as-the-Chief-Minister-in-2024.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-235513\" class=\" wp-image-235513\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-taking-oath-as-the-new-Deputy-Chief-Ministers-of-Bihar-under-the-leadership-of-Nitish-Kumar-as-the-Chief-Minister-in-2024.jpg\" alt=\"Vijay Kumar Sinha taking oath as the new Deputy Chief Ministers of Bihar, under the leadership of Nitish Kumar as the Chief Minister in 2024\" width=\"711\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-taking-oath-as-the-new-Deputy-Chief-Ministers-of-Bihar-under-the-leadership-of-Nitish-Kumar-as-the-Chief-Minister-in-2024.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-taking-oath-as-the-new-Deputy-Chief-Ministers-of-Bihar-under-the-leadership-of-Nitish-Kumar-as-the-Chief-Minister-in-2024-300x158.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/Vijay-Kumar-Sinha-taking-oath-as-the-new-Deputy-Chief-Ministers-of-Bihar-under-the-leadership-of-Nitish-Kumar-as-the-Chief-Minister-in-2024-768x404.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 711px) 100vw, 711px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-235513\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Vijay Kumar Sinha taking oath as the Deputy Chief Minister of Bihar, under the leadership of Nitish Kumar as the Chief Minister in 2024<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Car_Collection\"><\/span>Car Collection<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>He owns two Tavera Cars. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_235261_1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/myneta.info\/Bihar2020\/candidate.php?candidate_id=10071\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">MyNeta<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Assets_Liabilities\"><\/span>Assets &amp; Liabilities<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Movable_Assets\"><\/span><strong>Movable Assets<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Cash: Rs. 45,000<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Deposits in Banks: Rs. 4,520,220<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Bonds, Debentures and Shares: Rs 3,725,750<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Motor Vehicles: Rs. 464,827<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Jewellery: Rs. 3,50,000<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Other assets (Rifle &amp; Revolver): Rs. 77,181<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Immovable_Assets\"><\/span><strong>Immovable Assets<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Agricultural Land: Rs. 35,00,000<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Commercial Buildings: Rs 1,30,00,000<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Residential Buildings: Rs. 1,40,00,000<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Note: <\/strong>The given estimates of movable and immovable assets are according to the financial year 2020. It does not include the assets owned by his wife and dependents. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_235261_1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/myneta.info\/Bihar2020\/candidate.php?candidate_id=10071\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">MyNeta<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Net_Worth\"><\/span>Net Worth<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>In 2020, his net worth was Rs. 38,432,222. It does not include the net worth of his wife and dependents. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_235261_1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/myneta.info\/Bihar2020\/candidate.php?candidate_id=10071\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">MyNeta<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2016, he served as the President of the Governing Body of Rajeshwar Lal College (R.Lal College), Lakhisarai.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In March 2021, Sinha was criticized by the Opposition for his inadequate response to the mistreatment of an RJD and a Congress MLA on the premises of the Assembly after the House had passed the Special Armed Police Act. This Act expanded police authority to conduct warrantless searches and arrests, sparking protests from Opposition members. RJD MLAs responded by approaching Sinha&#8217;s seat, ripping up documents, and surrounding his office, effectively trapping him inside. The situation escalated to the point where the police had to intervene, physically removing the protesting MLAs, some of whom were forcibly taken away on stretchers.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A notable dispute between Sinha and Nitish occurred when Sinha excluded the Chief Minister&#8217;s name from the invitations for the Bihar Vidhan Sabha anniversary celebrations in July 2022. According to members of JD(U), this move was one of the triggers for Nitish to end his alliance with the BJP soon after.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2023, he took a vocal stand against the government on issues like the alleged ill-treatment of people from Bihar in Tamil Nadu. The government sent a team of officials to the southern state to look into the allegations and after these were found untrue, demanded an apology from the BJP leader.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_235261_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[+]<\/span><span><\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button collapsed\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_235261_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[\u2212]<\/span><\/p><\/div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container_235261_1\" class=\"collapsed\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">References<\/caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_235261_1_1\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_235261_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_1');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>1,<\/a> <a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_235261_1_2\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_235261_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_2');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>2<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/economictimes.indiatimes.com\/news\/politics-and-nation\/bihar-vijay-kumar-sinha-a-versatile-upper-caste-bjp-leader\/articleshow\/107204761.cms?from=mdr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Economic Times<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_235261_1_3\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_235261_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_3');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>3,<\/a> <a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_235261_1_4\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_235261_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_4');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>4,<\/a> <a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_235261_1_5\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_235261_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_235261_1_5');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>5<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/myneta.info\/Bihar2020\/candidate.php?candidate_id=10071\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">MyNeta<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n <\/tbody> <\/table> <\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Vijay Kumar Sinha is an Indian politician and a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP). He was elected MLA from Lakhisarai in 2005, 2010, 2015, and 2020. He held the position of Speaker in the Bihar Legislative Assembly from 2020 to 2022. He stepped down from this role after a no-confidence motion was moved against him by the then-ruling Mahagathbandhan. He has served as Leader of the Opposition Bihar Legislative Assembly (2022-2024) and Minister of Labour Resources Government of Bihar (2017-2020). He started serving as one of Bihar&#8217;s Deputy Chief Ministers in 2024, along with Samrat Choudhary sharing the <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":36,"featured_media":235512,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/235261"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/36"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=235261"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/235261\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":236447,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/235261\/revisions\/236447"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/235512"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=235261"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=235261"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=235261"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}